Welcome to The Hill’s Morning Report. . . . "On the Democratic side, Senate Minority Leader Charles Schumer (D-N.Y.) still hasn’t given up hope that multiple lower-tier Democratic presidential candidates will drop out and run for Senate in key states on the 2020 map. "As Alexander Bolton reports, in the wake of Rep. Eric Swalwell’s (D-Calif.) decision to drop out of the presidential race, Schumer is hoping former Rep. Beto O’Rourke (D-Texas), Montana Gov. Steve Bullock (D) and former Colorado Gov. John Hickenlooper (D) will take the hint and launch Senate bids in their respective states, all of which could become tough, competitive races if they were to do so. Of the three contests, only one — Colorado — is expected to be considered a top-tier Senate contest as Sen. Cory Gardner (R-Colo.) is believed to be the most vulnerable Senate Republican up for reelection."

Since 2004, when the first official party debates are before September, there were no major withdrawals within 30 days after that debate. This initially led me to the following: - "Zero" with a very high probability (70%) - "One or Two" with a moderately low probability (27%) as there tend to be 1-2 major withdrawals after the first official primary debates (when starting later in the year) that could be seen here - "Three or four" withdrawals was exceedingly unlikely (3%) but if 1-2 withdrawals occurred, there could be 1-2 follow-on withdrawals - Five or more was exceptionally improbable and rated as 0%

Evidence: -Ojeda dropping out in Jan 2019 -In 2008, 2 Dem. candidates withdrew before the primaries - both withdrew more than a month before or after the 1st debate -In 2008, 4 Rep. candidates withdrew before the primaries - all 4 withdrew more than a month after 1st debate -In 2012, 2 Rep. candidates withdrew before the primaries - both withdrew more than a month after 1st debate -In 2012, 1 Dem. candidate withdrew before the primaries - withdrew more than a month before 1st debate -In 2016, 3 Dem. candidates withdrew before the primaries - all 3 withdrew within a month of 1st debate -In 2016, 5 Rep. candidates withdrew before the primaries - all 5 withdrew more than a month after 1st debate -4 Dem. candidates would take a hit to their political reputation if they fail to move up in the coming weeks
